	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well I think you should re-evaluate your situation a little bit before you question your group value, above and beyond the Agro Management issues already posted.<br><br>First, below lvl 20 who is hitting for more than 20 with a weapon?&nbsp;&nbsp;Sure Rogues backstab for more and Casters can nuke hard but how hard is that Warrior hitting, he's still capped at 20 too except for criticals.  So you are doing all the melee damage they are.  The other classes will soon get duel wield I know, but even so it won't really crank up their damage output till post 20.<br><br>Next you have some nice spells, disease cloud is not only a taunt spell, but it prevents MOB regen.  That's not a big deal no as most fights take about 20 seconds tops, but later a MOB can regen 1k HPs during a fight if they don't have something like this on them to stop it.  You will also soon get the first installment of your Darkness Line, making you a snarer.  Your DOT's are on the way as well with a few nice debuffs, you may not spam the screen with damage but you definately do your share to a MOB.<br><br>USE THE PET!  The pet will add damage, and once you learn it's limitations, you can even pull with it up.  Just park it behind the group far enough that it's agro range doesn't include where the MOBs are.  Then as you pull, the pet won't agro till you get back to the group anyway (it has a limited range where it will run to assist you).  You could also just let another melee pull for the group, since you don't have FD now you have no advantage over the Warriors when pulling at this point.  The pet will do reasonable damage for a DOT, especially if you give it a 2 hand weapon.  Always go high damage with pet weapons as the delay is ignored by the pet anyway.  You can also give the pet a shield, this has a coolness value but also helps the pet survive the occasional rippost and seems to add bash damage once he gets bash.<br><br>While you have no real dd spells, your lifetaps should be counted for double damage when you look at their usefulness.  They save the healers mana, hurt the MOB and generally keep the group pulling longer between med breaks.<br><br>SK's contribute plenty in groups, not just agro.  Learn all the skills you have and how to emply them best.  As you progress learn which spells will do the most good in a veriety of situations, sometimes you want agro, sometimes you don't.  Your debuffs add alot to the groups abilities later on, and eventually we become the best Pullers in the game with a near instant FD and BE Greaves for when it fails.  Eventually you should learn the arts of pulling MOBs, always trying to get the single without having to FD pull, when you truely master this skill you will stop asking what your value to a group is.<br><br>Just keep at it, and keep the melee damage in perspective.  Post lvl 25 with a MoSS we can almost keep up with the duel wielders in melee damage for a while, but we will fall behind.  Just remember the other things we bring to a fight, we don't rely excusively for melee damage for our worth.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
